Epidemic measles in an isolated unvaccinated population, India. Between June and September, 1986, an outbreak of measles occurred in Pilkhi Primary Health Centre area (population 56,000) in Tehri Garhwal district, Uttar Pradesh, India. Overall, 1092 cases were identified and 62 died case-fatality ratio was 5.7%. Illness was restricted primarily to children below 15 years of age